title: Vinicius Jr renews attack on authorities after racist abuse and reveals death threats
description: Real Madrid star Vinicius Jr has renewed his attack on La Liga and the Spanish authorities, revealing he received death threats this season.

title: Man accused of Idaho student murders refuses to enter plea
description: A man accused of stabbing to death four university students in their beds in Idaho last year has refused to enter a plea after appearing in court.

title: Toddler, 3, shoots murder suspect and his own mother
description: A three-year-old has grabbed a gun and shot a murder suspect and his own mother in the US state of Indiana.

title: Ireland to become first country in the world to put health warnings on alcohol
description: Ireland is set to become the first country in the world to put health warnings on alcohol products.

title: Smashed Kurt Cobain guitar sells for almost £500,000
description: An electric guitar smashed by Kurt Cobain in a recording studio has sold for almost £500,000 at auction.

title: At least 19 students killed in fire at school dormitory in Guyana
description: At least 19 students have been killed in a fire at a secondary school dormitory in Guyana in South America, authorities have said.

title: Former minister under ex-Egyptian president Hosni Mubarak donates £5m to Tories
description: An ex-minister to former Egyptian president Hosni Mubarak has donated £5m to the Conservatives to help them fight the next election.

title: Police investigating Madeleine McCann disappearance to search reservoir in Portugal
description: Police investigating the disappearance of Madeleine McCann are to carry out new searches of a reservoir, Sky News understands.

title: China bans comedian Uncle Roger over series of jokes
description: A Malaysian comedian has had his Chinese social media account suspended after poking fun at China in one of his shows.

title: Ukraine says its troops are still advancing on devastated city of Bakhmut
description: Ukraine has said its troops are still advancing on the flanks of the devastated city of Bakhmut, but that the "intensity" of their movement has decreased.

title: Meta hit with record £1bn fine
description: The owner of WhatsApp, Instagram and Facebook has been slapped with a record fine of €1.2bn (£1.04bn) by the Irish data protection regulator.

title: Meteor burns through skies creating a sonic boom
description: The skies above northern Queensland were set alight by a meteor which blazed through the atmosphere and caused a sonic boom.

title: China bans US chipmaker as tech row with US escalates
description: Beijing has stepped up its feud with Washington after announcing products made by US memory chip giant Micron Technology pose a national security risk.
